World championship Signature Event
Seaquam Robotics
WHY THIS SPONSORSHIP MATTERS
Seaquam Secondary's robotics program is a dynamic community of over 60 students who come together
to represent our school in Vex Robotics Competition tournaments across North America. Our program is
rooted in an exceptionally competitive spirit, with students pushing themselves and their teammates to
achieve their best in every competition. But our program is much more than just a competitive team.
For many students, it is a place where they can pursue their passion for robotics and collaborate with
like-minded peers. Our robotics program is composed of over 15 teams, each working on their own
unique projects and challenges. But despite the individual focus of each team, students uplift each
other and work together to achieve outstanding results. The results of our program speak for
themselves. Over the years, we have achieved remarkable success in competitions across North
America, including at the VEX Robotics World Championship in Dallas, TX. In fact, we are proud to have
qualified four teams to compete in this prestigious event, where we personally will showcase our skills
and compete against some of the best robotics teams in the world.
(Our program at the 2022 Vex Robotics World Championships in Dallas texas)
2
WHO IS 9181M
9181M is a competitive robotics team made up of three members: Joshua Gilevich, Vincent Chung, and
Michael Lange. Joshua and Vincent have been competing in robotics for five years, while Michael is a
newcomer to the team this year. Over the past year, we have participated in seven tournaments,
consistently demonstrating our skills and determination. Through these competitions, we have
established ourselves as one of the top performers In British Colombia. Our hard work and dedication
paid off when we reached the finals of the regional championships (that qualifies for the world
championship), where we earned an impressive second-place finish. This achievement is a testament to
our competitive spirit and the strength of our team.
THE OBJECTIVE
● The purpose of this sponsorship is to receive funding to participate in The VEX Robotics World
Championships signature event in Dallas Texas.
● By attending the event in texas, we will be able to compete against and connect with teams
and like-minded robotics students from around the world.
● Competing in a more elite environment will help us forge more bonds as a team and as a
program (there are 4 other Seaquam teams currently planning to attend).
● We will also have the opportunity to bring back awards for our program and potentially end up
on the news
GOALS
1. Try to connect with as many teams at World championships
2. Promote your sponsorship at worlds by doing some kind of collaborative merch like a t-shirt
with your logo and our program's logo or a banner with your logo that we can hang in the pits
3. Receive judged awards and potentially win the tournament

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
Awards received
- Excellence award (most prestigious award given at a tournament. It means you are
the best team at the competition)
- Tournament finalist x 3 ( it means you made it to overall finals where you can get
crowned tournament champion or if you lose you get finalist) in finals there are only
four other teams out of the 60 - 70 teams that go. You are also in a two-team alliance
during elimination rounds so it is considered 2nd place
(this picture was taken on March 5th, 2023 during the regional championships finals)
- Design award ( this award means that you have one of the best design robots at the
tournament)
- Judges award x 2 ( an award given to a team who is recognized by the judges to have
special attributes it does not have to follow the award criteria)
- Amaze award (a runner-up to the excellence award, basically the 2nd best team at the
competition
